    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "TWA",
      "TWA-Trans World Airlines\nBoeing 727-231A\nOver 1800 727's have been produced, making it the world's\nbest selling jetliner.\nThe majority\nare 727-200 \"stretch\"\nversions, 20 feet longer than the original model, and carrying\n30 or more additional passengers. TWA's first -231 entered\nservice in 1968.\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nB-050\n85933-D\npost card\nPhoto courtesy Trans-World Airlines\nN54341 c/n 21628\n2001.106.214"
